social_posts.post_text:
On Tuesday night we lost our little Abbie. She was the queen of the house and ruled us all. 

Abbie was 19 years fierce when she left us and a 3lb. dog who knew no fear. 

She would sit next to my head in bed and slap my face with her little paw if I was not sleeping in the appropriate cuddle position. Abbie made sure her demands were met, and if I was too stupid to figure them out then she made sure that A) I knew that, and B) she wasn’t above spelling it out for me. She put me through extensive training to be her household staff.

I’m grateful for the almost two decades I had with her, but my heart breaks to say goodbye after we lost Zoe just under 5 weeks ago.

Abbie will always be remembered and always missed, but she’s with her sister now and I am sure getting them both into some wonderful trouble on the other side of the rainbow bridge.

Cheers and a very Merry Christmas to all who observe this tradition and happy holidays for anyone finding reason to celebrate this December. 🥂 

I am so grateful for my family who have been my strength and joy. These are the people closest to me, who challenge me, inspire me, and keep me laughing. 🙏

My Christmas wish always has and always will be this! 🎄

Checking out @theimmersivekingtut exhibit in LA… love diving into history and the ability to explore Tut’s tomb through VR was incredible. 

I also got a new book about the female pharaohs that I can’t wait to start! 📖

Had a wonderful weekend in Cambria, CA soaking up some summer sun and fresh sea air. We also visited the gorgeous Hearst Castle. 🌺

Today is the road trip home and tomorrow is back to reality, but this was a lovely escape.

Hope you all are having a great week! 😎

Absolutely loved seeing this show at the @hollywoodpantagestheatre - bravo to the cast, crew, and musicians who made this experience so magnificent. 👑

I loved the historical references, the female empowerment, and the extremely relatable modern day comparisons. 💕

Cheers to freedom and unity! On this Juneteenth, we raise our glasses high to celebrate the emancipation of all and honor the resilience of those who fought for justice. 😃

Let's toast to progress, equality, and a future where every voice is heard and cherished. 🥂

Happy Juneteenth, a day of reflection, empowerment, and love for all! 💕

🗽 Celebrating Independence Day with a touch of history and a call to action! 

🇺🇸 'Let us not seek the Republican answer or the Democratic answer, but the right answer. Let us not seek to fix the blame for the past. Let us accept our own responsibility for the future.' - John F. Kennedy. 

Your voice matters – so pay attention not only to what politicians say but more importantly what they do and what they are convicted of. Then vote for progress and a better tomorrow! 🗳️💙

Our family grew and we have furbabies! 🐶

So grateful for this family and our recently adopted additions! Foxy is a Pomeranian mix and she is so sweet and loyal, the perfect woman’s best friend dog. Bucky is a young mutt and totally rambunctious… definitely keeps us on our toes. 💕

We’re pretty sure Zoe sent us Foxy and Abbie sent us Bucky and we couldn’t be happier! 😁

Summoning the Halloween Magic today. We have our Jack O’lantern to scare away the ghouls and plenty of treats planned for this evening. 🎃 

Wishing you all a spook-tacular Halloween full of hauntingly good fun! 👻

#halloween2023 #happyhalloween🎃👻 #jackolanterns
From our family to you and yours- Merry Christmas! 🎄🎁

Happy new year everyone! 🍾

Thank you for giving us so many memories and laughter in 2023. Our best hope is to keep the good times rolling in 2024. 🥂

Wishing you all a new year filled with peace, laughter, and adventure ❤️

🎬 Co-host @wearedefinitelynotdefinitive
